Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.00,0:00:12.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I am a recognized authority\Non the 4.5 tatami room.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.62,0:00:15.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I think I shall expound on\Nthe aspects of that space.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.24,0:00:18.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Although I knew of one person\Nwho lived in a 3 tatami room,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.33,0:00:20.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}they grew more and more stubbornly\Nset against the tides of the world,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.50,0:00:23.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and last year their parents came\Nfrom their hometown to pick them up.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.00,0:00:25.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It might be a little hard to\Nbelieve, but near Joudo Temple{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.20,0:00:28.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I've heard there are rooms that exist\Nwith two tatami mats laid end-to-end.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.37,0:00:31.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If you slept on them every night,\Nthere's no doubt you'd grow in height.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.63,0:00:35.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In Kitashirakawa Baptist General Hospital's\NXXXX ward, it's said there are 1 tatami rooms,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.66,0:00:38.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but the students that knew of this\Nended up mysteriously disappearing,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.37,0:00:40.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and their friends one by\None all met unfortunate fates.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.40,0:00:44.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And then there is the 4.5 tatami room.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.05,0:00:52.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Compared to the 1, 2, or 3 tatami rooms,\Nthe 4.5 tatami room is a truly beautiful square.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.15,0:00:57.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Is it not magnificent? {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.11,0:01:00.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}2 tatamis can also form\Na square, but it is cramped.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.08,0:01:02.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}On the other hand, once you've\Nmade a square larger than 4.5 tatami,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.87,0:01:06.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}it becomes as spacious as Takeda Shingen's\Nlavatory, and one might even get lost.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.12,0:01:10.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}After entering university, I became\Na fierce supporter of the 4.5 tatami room.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.37,0:01:12.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Those people who live in\N7, 8, or even 10 tatami rooms...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.88,0:01:15.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Are they truly worthy of ruling\Nover such a space as if it is their own?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.83,0:01:17.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I wonder if human beings\Neven have such capacity?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.86,0:01:21.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We humanity have the ability to\Nrule 4.5 tatami and smaller spaces.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.79,0:01:23.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Those reprehensible beings\Nwho greedily lust for larger area{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.89,0:01:26.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}will surely be met by fearsome\Nrebellion from some corner of their room.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.66,0:01:28.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That was my assertion. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.89,0:01:31.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The 4.5 tatami room is my entire world.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.00,0:01:33.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That is my conviction, but now...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.50,0:01:35.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...there is also the objective\Nreality of the situation.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.28,0:01:38.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Where is the person responsible?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.45,0:01:42.70,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The Tatami Galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.37,0:03:10.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Then I was a freshman university student{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.79,0:03:14.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and before me lay open countless\Ndoors to various different campus lives.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.29,0:03:16.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But I didn't join any of the circles.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.41,0:03:18.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A rose-colored campus life is, after all,\Nnothing more than an illusory dream.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.91,0:03:22.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I decided to train myself in the tranquil\Nspace known as the 4.5 tatami room.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.50,0:03:28.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Terayama Shuji once said this:\N"Throw away books and go out into the city."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.58,0:03:30.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But what was he saying to do\Nonce you go out into the city?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.99,0:03:34.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}For the next two years I spent\Nmost of my time in the 4.5 tatami room,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.25,0:03:36.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and some people came to call\Nme the "4.5 Tatami Ideologue."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.90,0:03:48.12,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The 4.5 Tatami Ideologue
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.72,0:03:52.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is my inner sanctum. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.87,0:03:56.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Eizan train runs behind it, and though it\Nonly takes a few seconds to circle this space,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.04,0:03:57.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}everything about me is crammed in here.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.70,0:04:00.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}To the north is a cheap, flimsy door.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.20,0:04:03.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A note with venerable hints from the\Nprevious occupant is still affixed there.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.50,0:04:05.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}On one side of the door\Nis a sink of bottomless filth,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.87,0:04:08.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}assuring the loss of any\Nwould-be cook's motivation.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.29,0:04:10.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I steadfastly refuse to try my hand at cooking,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.75,0:04:13.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}putting into practice my belief that\N"men shouldn't set foot in the kitchen."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.75,0:04:16.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The majority of the north wall is a closet,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.00,0:04:20.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}filled carelessly with unremarkable\Nclothing and books I never read.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.00,0:04:22.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My library of obscenity is also within.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.00,0:04:27.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In one corner of the east wall are\Na vacuum cleaner and rice cooker{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.41,0:04:29.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}that do not look as if\Nthey've been heavily used,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.25,0:04:30.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and most of the wall is a grand library,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.91,0:04:33.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}in which an enormous number of\Nprinted works have been assembled.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.29,0:04:37.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In the space between the\Nsoutheast bookcase and my desk{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.50,0:04:40.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}lies an area in which\Nvarious junk has been thrown,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.04,0:04:42.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and I believe if one were to\Nventure into it alone and get lost,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.33,0:04:44.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the chances of returning alive would be slim.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.16,0:04:48.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And then from the south to the southwest{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.08,0:04:50.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}there is a window which rattles\Nas the Eizan train passes by,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.54,0:04:54.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and there underneath it is placed my desk\Nthat has been with me through high school.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.75,0:04:57.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In the west are socks\Nin search of lost partners,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.25,0:05:00.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the clothes that make up my everyday\Nlife, and an old-fashioned world map.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.04,0:06:02.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A famous short story begins with a normal\Nman that one morning turns into an insect.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.62,0:06:05.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}For me it was not something so dramatic.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.00,0:06:06.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But it had definitely become a problem.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.16,0:06:11.75,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}A proper man shall not be perturbed no matter\Nwhat circumstances he might find himself in.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.75,0:06:13.06,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}He must think through the situation calmly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.40,0:06:16.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But as I had not had much\Nenthusiasm for going outside previously,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.08,0:06:19.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}wouldn't going crazy trying to get\Nout make me quite shallow as a human?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.87,0:06:21.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}While I sat down and calmly waited it out,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.31,0:06:23.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the situation might well\Nchange for the better on its own.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.85,0:06:55.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I had come up with a single hypothesis.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.51,0:06:57.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It supposed that this was a\Ncurse of that old fortune teller.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.58,0:07:01.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There was an old woman who emitted\Nfreely an eerie aura as I passed by Kiyamachi.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.85,0:07:04.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The old woman said "Student\Nthere, you'll be in trouble soon!"{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.04,0:07:06.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"You have made a false step in life!"{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.78,0:07:10.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I replied "That is not the case at all!\NI am satisfied with the way I live!"{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.66,0:07:13.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But the old woman continued,\N"You shouldn't be so stubborn."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.58,0:07:16.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"I can sense you have talent, so there\Nis opportunity dangling before your eyes."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.29,0:07:22.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That is not an opportunity or anything!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.50,0:07:24.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Finally the old woman went\N"Heh, heh, heh, heh, heh..."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.96,0:07:27.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Or maybe not, but she smiled evilly like that.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.62,0:08:05.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, is anybody there?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.35,0:08:09.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}As I cried out a line straight out of\Nsome crappy drama to no response,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.16,0:08:11.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I had no choice but to take all\Nthe embarrassment upon myself.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.75,0:08:23.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Well, it seems we've finally\Nentered the realm of science fiction.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.92,0:08:25.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I have a feeling there was once a movie{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.54,0:08:27.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}where someone was trapped\Nin rooms connected in this way.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.23,0:08:33.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Since water flows out, that means it should\Nbe connected to the outside world in some way.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.41,0:08:36.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If I were some kind of mole-man\Nand could pass through the faucet,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.00,0:08:38.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I could struggle through to\NKyoto Water Bureau, but...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.54,0:08:43.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}After two days or so, I ran out of food.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.08,0:08:47.54,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,A source of protein?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.08,0:08:47.54,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Protein?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.29,0:08:54.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I was like a Robinson Crusoe washed\Nup on a deserted 4.5 tatami room.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.83,0:08:56.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But for me there was a faucet\Nwith water, and furniture...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.80,0:09:00.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I had a set of everything; I could\Nhardly call this a state of survival.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.81,0:09:02.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I had a stroke of good luck. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.91,0:09:05.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In the 4.5 room next door there\Nwere fishburgers and a castella.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.90,0:09:07.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So then, is it okay for me to eat this?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.84,0:09:09.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I don't really read much science fiction,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.33,0:09:10.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}so if this really is that sort of phenomenon,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.82,0:09:13.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}would eating this castella\Ncause some sort of harm?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.66,0:09:18.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And if this is all some sort of\Nhallucination, is this castella even real?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.33,0:09:24.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It is a castella. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.50,0:09:27.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Putting aside rational explanation,\Nthis was indeed an honest to goodness castella.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.58,0:09:30.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And so the problem of my\Nfood supply was basically solved.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.46,0:09:32.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}As I could not see the light of the sun,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.08,0:09:33.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I could not determine\Nwhether it was noon or night,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.83,0:09:36.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and though I made it a point to\Ndelineate each day from the next,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.04,0:09:37.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I could not be sure that\Nmy delineations were correct.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.54,0:09:49.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I can't ignore the nutrients\Nthat I get from the castella.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.16,0:09:51.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I got it a few days ago\Nfrom a person named Ozu,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.58,0:09:54.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}who came to visit a person\Nwho lives on the second floor.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.20,0:09:55.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A couple of days before I became trapped,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.16,0:09:59.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I discovered a large cockroach\Noutbreak in our Shimogamo Yuusuisou.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.25,0:10:51.25,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,I come and go to the\Nroom on the second floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.25,0:10:53.25,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,I made a cockroach cube\Nweapon but it malfunctioned.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.25,0:10:55.54,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,- Sorry for the inconvenience. Please, eat this.\N- Ozu
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.17,0:10:59.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}At the time I felt an\Nirrational anger come over me.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.91,0:11:03.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But should I not be thankful to this Ozu\Nperson now that I am in this circumstance?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.18,0:11:05.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There were times I despaired,\Nbut after I thought about it,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.28,0:11:07.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}perhaps this situation could\Nbe called a stroke of luck?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.12,0:11:10.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If I transfer to the room next door I can\Nget another castella and more fishburgers.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.19,0:11:11.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I might be getting lopsided nutrition,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.68,0:11:14.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but food would not be a\Nproblem in the foreseeable future.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.19,0:11:15.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}With things as they are, {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.58,0:11:18.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I could think of this world of 4.5 tatami\Nrooms as a wonderful place to live.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.92,0:11:21.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}From a physical perspective a\N4.5 tatami space is quite small,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.33,0:11:23.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but one can find an expansive\Ninner world from within.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.70,0:11:25.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Within the world of imagination\Nthere are no boundaries.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.91,0:11:29.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It could be said that I am the\Nultimate Creator of this 4.5 tatami room!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.46,0:11:32.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I will survive. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.67,0:11:35.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I will have fun persisting in\Nthis perfect 4.5 tatami world!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.64,0:11:37.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That way I will show this\Ngod of fate who is boss!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.83,0:11:39.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I trembled with excitement! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.84,0:11:42.86,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,This is coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.66,0:11:53.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I thought that I might take this\Nopportunity to read the books I had not read.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.83,0:11:55.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I have as much time as I need! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.44,0:11:59.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is fun! This is fun! This is fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.29,0:12:16.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sometimes to pass the time\NI would admirably think to study,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.37,0:12:19.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but Schrödinger's equation knocked me out.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.07,0:12:24.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}As a pioneer in this 4.5 tatami world,\NI wove a plan to bravely make my life here.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.83,0:12:27.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I would devise ways to use the castella\Nand fishburgers to make various other dishes.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.55,0:12:29.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I would undertake operation of a\Nsystematic system of growing mushrooms!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.79,0:12:32.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I would even remodel many of\Nthe rooms into a bowling alley,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.20,0:12:34.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}or movie theater, or arcade, and create\Nall kinds of different amusement centers!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.78,0:12:36.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I would realize my own Utopia! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.04,0:12:37.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Just thinking about it made me excited!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.25,0:12:52.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even doing something as shameful as this,\Nno one in the world would pay any heed.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.33,0:12:54.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I will not be pestered by other people.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.16,0:12:55.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It is indeed a world just for myself.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.37,0:13:02.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Absorbing myself in reading\N20,000 Leagues Under the Sea,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.21,0:13:04.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I got drunk on cheap whiskey\Nand cried out toward the ceiling.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.96,0:13:08.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Becoming afraid of the silent\Nworld pressing down around me,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.08,0:13:10.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I sang all the songs\NI knew at the top of my lungs.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.41,0:13:14.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And so I discovered that I myself\Nwanted to escape from this 4.5 tatami world.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.54,0:13:18.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I didn't want to admit, but I was completely\Nand utterly sick of this 4.5 tatami room.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.33,0:13:21.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If I opened the door to the dirty\Nhallway and headed down that dirty hallway,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.07,0:13:23.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}there would be the dirty\Nbathroom, and the dirty shoe boxes,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.16,0:13:25.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and then I could exit the\Nboarding house to the outside.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.23,0:13:27.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It was because I could always\Ngo outside when I pleased{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.50,0:13:29.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}that I confined myself to the 4.5 tatami room.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.49,0:13:35.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The most real thing to me was a single\Nphysiological need I was struggling with.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.08,0:13:37.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}To put it plainly, I couldn't stand the smell.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.54,0:13:38.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}One day I couldn't stand it anymore,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.81,0:13:39.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and I hastily left on a journey {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.87,0:13:41.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and I hastily left on a journey{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.87,0:13:43.51,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Lavatory
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.34,0:13:42.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}to get far away from that room.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.51,0:13:47.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It must have been a week since I'd\Nbeen trapped in this mysterious world.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.04,0:13:49.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Anyway, let's see how far\Nthese 4.5 tatami rooms go...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.75,0:14:00.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That day I must have traversed\Nover 1004.5 tatami rooms,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.29,0:14:01.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and yet they still continued. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.58,0:14:03.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Eventually I felt like a fool. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.86,0:14:08.36,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Alchemy
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.47,0:14:11.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When I went searching in\Nthe space between my desk{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.26,0:14:13.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and bookshelf known as the\N"Siberian Penal Colony,"{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.08,0:14:14.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I found a thin little wallet. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.62,0:14:19.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If each 4.5 tatami room has 1000 yen,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.91,0:14:22.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}each time I move to another\Nroom I get another 1000 yen.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.08,0:14:24.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If I move to 10 rooms,\Nor 100 rooms, or 1000 rooms...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.00,0:14:48.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I made a curious discovery. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.70,0:14:52.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}While taking a break I thought to read\NThe Curious Casebook of Inspector Hanshichi,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.25,0:14:55.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}which I had bought at a used book fair,\Nbut it didn't exist in that 4.5 tatami room.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.37,0:14:58.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The collections on each bookshelf\Nwere different, if only slightly.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.54,0:15:01.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I noticed that although at a glance\Nthe 4.5 tatami rooms seemed identical,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.62,0:15:03.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}they were each slightly different.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.08,0:15:18.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it was all a dream!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.73,0:15:22.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I wonder why I hadn't thought\Nto break through the wall?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.37,0:15:26.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}After all, the walls are thin enough to be\Nable to hear the conversations next door.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.98,0:15:30.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Chinese exchange student next\Ndoor would often bring his girlfriend,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.33,0:15:32.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and they'd whisper sweet nothings to each other.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.12,0:15:33.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I regretted from the bottom of my heart{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.91,0:15:36.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}that I had not studied Chinese\Nas my second foreign language.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.66,0:15:39.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even if I broke through the wall and invaded,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.12,0:15:42.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm sure he could just laugh it off with\Nthe deep tolerance of one from the mainland.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.25,0:15:43.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Here we go! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.27,0:16:03.77,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Day xxx
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.20,0:16:25.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Could it be that I was dead? {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.79,0:16:27.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Had I fallen into a so-called 4.5 tatami hell,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.79,0:16:31.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}forced to suffer for all eternity?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.80,0:16:36.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's hard to believe... The leaves are\Nprobably turning by now on the outside.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.20,0:16:38.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I had not eaten out for more than 1200 hours,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.75,0:16:41.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}nor bathed in the sun's rays,\Nnor breathed fresh air,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.04,0:16:42.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}nor spoken with another human being!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.66,0:16:47.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In this room was something I did not remember.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.31,0:16:53.32,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucky Cat Chinese Restaurant
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.12,0:16:49.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It seemed to be the signboard for some organization.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.50,0:16:51.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Why did the 4.5 tatami\Nrooms have these differences?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.91,0:16:56.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}They should all be my same 4.5 tatami room,\Nso what gave rise to these small differences?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.12,0:17:00.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In that instant I grasped the\Nstructure of this 4.5 tatami world.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.50,0:17:02.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The bookshelves with books\NI had missed a chance to buy,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.66,0:17:04.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}circles which I shouldn't\Nhave been a member of...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.41,0:17:07.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I see! These are my parallel worlds!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.70,0:17:09.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In these how many tens of days, {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.75,0:17:12.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I had been crossing through\Nparallel universes of 4.5 tatami rooms{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.92,0:17:15.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}for each of the various\Nchoices I could have made!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.62,0:17:35.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is the dental hygienist Hanuki-san.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.54,0:17:38.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The previous autumn I'd heard\Nrumors of a beautiful dental hygienist{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.58,0:17:40.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}that gave the most excellent gum massages,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.54,0:17:42.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and so I'd visited the local dentist.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.87,0:17:46.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Lately I've seen a drunk\NHanuki-san looking completely different{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.64,0:17:48.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}yelling over the railing of the Mikage bridge.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.62,0:17:51.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I wonder what happened to that\Ncool professional demeanor of hers?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.91,0:17:55.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But a mental ruffian such as myself\Nwas not able to grasp the subtlety of it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.01,0:17:58.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I wonder what choice I made? {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.29,0:18:00.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In this world I was close to Hanuki-san,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.20,0:18:01.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I lived together with a beautiful love-doll,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.83,0:18:04.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and I even seemed to have\Nexchanged letters with a proper lady.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.25,0:18:06.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It was a situation I could only dream of.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.52,0:18:09.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This one looked like a lifestyle\Nthat had fallen into depravity.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.77,0:18:11.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Almost like I had become the disciple{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.37,0:18:13.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}of that person on the second floor\Nof the Shimogamo Yuusuisou.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.91,0:18:17.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I threw away my backpack\Nfilled with 1000 yen bills.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.45,0:18:20.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's not like I would ever make use of it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.66,0:18:29.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}T-This is...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.62,0:18:31.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Funds for continuing the Proxy War?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.20,0:18:37.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The occupant of this room seemed\Nlike they reached toward the heavens.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.79,0:18:39.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I remembered feeling somewhat afraid.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.79,0:18:42.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Did I search for an even\Ngreater happiness than this?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.10,0:18:44.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Isn't that almost like\NIcarus flying toward the sun?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.79,0:18:49.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Come to think of it, I recall seeing\Na flier about something like this.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.12,0:18:56.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Isn't this that fellow I've seen at Neko Ramen?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.61,0:19:01.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's rumored that Neko Ramen uses actual\Ncats in its broth, but the taste is unmatched.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.44,0:19:06.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It was a calm conversation\Nthat reminded me of youth.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.96,0:19:11.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I overheard the two worrying about who\Nwould succeed them in continuing some battle,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.54,0:19:13.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but one of them was a fine specimen of a man{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.50,0:19:17.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}while the other was a resident of Shimogamo\NYuusuisou with a face like an eggplant.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.13,0:19:20.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I usually thought of that man as\Nsomeone I did not want to associate with.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.14,0:19:25.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But to think it was that ladies'\Nman who had such a "hobby"...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.70,0:19:32.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}For some strange reason I began to feel\Nattached to these people I barely knew.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.04,0:19:35.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I felt as if Id known them a long time, yet\Nall that remained was this feeling of nostalgia.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.41,0:19:41.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you get paid?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.12,0:19:42.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't the cameraman hit on you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.75,0:19:48.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Not having a single person make fun of me\Nfor doing a thing like this was hard to take.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.45,0:19:51.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If there were some slippery\Nevil companion here with me...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.08,0:19:52.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think you're doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.70,0:19:55.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are there maggots crawling\Naround your cerebral cortex?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.62,0:19:58.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...I'm sure they would have\Ncompletely belittled me like that.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.79,0:20:11.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And yet every occupant of\Nevery room seemed to be having fun.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.79,0:20:13.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even if it wasn't rose-colored,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.58,0:20:17.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I could see each 4.5 tatami\Nroom had its own color to it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.00,0:20:19.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Was it possible for me to have\Nmade these choices, I wonder?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.04,0:20:32.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, it's me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.87,0:20:49.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.62,0:20:51.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Help me, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.70,0:20:56.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But I had already realized. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.87,0:20:59.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My fate would change from\Neven the tiniest of choices.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.62,0:21:00.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}An innumerable number of I's are born,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.91,0:21:02.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}an innumerable number of\N4.5 tatami rooms are born.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.58,0:21:05.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In other words, theoretically\Nthis 4.5 tatami world has no end!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.45,0:21:16.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Anyway, it seems like these fellows\Ncan cross through the parallel worlds{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.04,0:21:17.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and gather in them one after another.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.66,0:21:20.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}They can lose their heart with love\Nor liven it up with raunchy stories.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.83,0:21:23.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}On the contrary, I only\Ntell raunchy stories to myself,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.33,0:21:25.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}always absorbed in my solitary delusions.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.08,0:21:26.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But that can no longer continue.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.76,0:21:28.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
